 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Ammar</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> My kids dont fight as much as you all do. If I could put you all in Timeout I would.</P><P>What we are discussing is first, what can be done to improve casters in general, improving their damage ratio over melee to what it was once before.  This is balancing.  Suggestions here should be general ideas that can be beneficial to ALL pure casters.  To me this seems real simple:</P><P>- Items that reduce:  casting time, mana cost, DoT duration (same dmg, shorter duration), and maybe refresh time.</P><P>- Items that increase:  damage done, casting range, and effect duration.</P><P>These type of improvements would be similar to the improvements melee PCs get from better weapons.  Im sure there are many other ideas along these lines, but they should address all casters.</P><P>Secondly, we should address that which is applicable to Necros only.  What can be done to improve our effectiveness in raid situations without over powering us in solo situations.  Come on now, we are currently pretty dang effective solo. I see two areas that should be addressed to fix this.</P><P>- DoT stacking:  This is a no-brainer and should have been fixed years ago.  The arguments have all been made and Ive yet to hear a single valid reason this should not be fixed.  But if it is such a problem, as a minimum, enable DoT stacking in raid zones.<BR>- Pet pathing:  If the pathing is to difficult to fix then give all pet classes the ability to control their pets.  The level 60 skill (/pet hold) is a joke in that it should be a command available from level 1.  Suck up your pride Verant and admit this was and has been a problem from day one and fix it. </P><P>The key here is to keep it simple.  Simple problems can normally be solved with simple solutions.  The hardest part is always first admitting there is a problem.  Once that is done, put your pride in your pocket and fix it.</P><P>Ammar - 54 Heretic<BR>Drinal</P><P><BR> </font></td>
